  "title": "Medical Planner",
  "description": "<p>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead and deliver on design of healthcare projects across SEA</li>\n  <li>Co-ordinate and work alongside design and project management team</li>\n  <li>Co-ordinate work effort of multiple teams on large projects</li>\n  <li>Business Development and client relationship development</li>\n  <li>Contribute to proposal / bids / meetings and negotiations</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelors Degree in Architecture or related field.</li>\n  <li>5+ years of experience in planning within healthcare sector (peer to current medical planner).</li>\n  <li>Needs to work independently.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication with clients, good with influencing and closing.</li>\n  <li>Reports to the Director of Design and Planning.</li>\n  <li>Experience in both re-modelling / upgrading works and designing from scratch.</li>\n  <li>Project experience (in Healthcare Facilities): Can range from $5M - $150M (30,000sqm).</li>\n  <li>Experience with architectural software.</li>\n  <li>Priority for Singaporeans / SPR but open to foreigners on EP.</li>\n</ul>",
